As of 17:52 p.m. on March 5, there were 25,275 confirmed cases, 80,568 confirmed cases, and 522 suspected cases, according to Dr. Syzygium aromaticum's real time data. There were 5952 severe cases, 3016 deaths and 52277 cured cases.

As of March 4, there were 12,668 confirmed cases and 214 deaths worldwide, excluding China, according to the World Health Organization. With the exception of China, there are currently 76 countries with newly diagnosed cases of pneumonia.

Development of epidemic situation

Patient dies after discharge from hospital. The patient, Li Liang, a 36-year-old Chinese medicine doctor (without a medical license) at an Orthopaedic Rehabilitation Clinic, had mild symptoms, Caixin reported. He developed fever on 3 February, was admitted to a community isolation site on 8 February, tested positive for the new crown nucleic acid on 9 February, and was transferred to Guobo Square hospital in Hanyang on 12 February for treatment with pure Chinese medicine. His fever was reduced and his cough was relieved. On February 20 and February 23, Li Liang underwent two nucleic acid tests in the shelter hospital, both negative, no oxygen uptake index oxygen saturation is more than 95% , on February 26, "discharged after assessment by the Expert Group, " into the community isolation point isolation for 14 days, and then I went back to drinking Chinese medicine.

On Feb. 28, Li felt his mouth was dry. His wife recalled, "the doctor told him that his mouth was dry because he was taking Chinese medicine and told him to drink more water. So Li bought a lot of water and fruit to eat in his room. " On the morning of March 2, li Liang's wife and Li Liang video call, said "the temperature is only 35.3 degrees, " a weak pulse, lying in bed without energy. At 3:30 pm, the isolation point called Li Liang "stress, bad spirit" , at 5:08 Li Liang died in isolation hotel. The three causes of death recorded in the medical certificate of death are: New Pneumonia, sudden death by respiratory obstruction and respiratory circulatory failure. Whether he did not meet the discharge criteria to be released from the shelter, or belongs to the Fuyang is not conclusive. Several shelter hospitals in Wuhan have stopped discharging patients.

Government bans face masks in Florida, pushing the limit to 6,000. According to Yonhap News Agency, as of March 5 at 16:00, South Korea confirmed a total of 6,088 cases, 41 deaths, an increase of 322 cases compared with 0:00 on March 5,96 countries and regions have adopted entry restrictions on South Korea. The South Korean government plans to increase production of masks, limit exports and limit people to two a week in order to ease the demand for masks, and plans to increase the number of masks sold in public channels such as pharmacies, post offices and farmers'associations supermarkets, from 50% of the market to 80% . Taiwan has taken similar steps before.

Hong Kong has seen the world's first case of a dog infected with the virus, possibly from humans. On the evening of March 4, the Agriculture, Fisheries and Conservation Department of Hong Kong announced that the specimen of a pet dog of a patient with new coronavirus tested weakly positive for several times. However, the dog does not have any new crown-related symptoms. Laboratory tests on the dog's oral and nasal specimens on 26 February, 28 February and 2 March were weakly positive for novel coronavirus. Experts from the public health of the University of Hong Kong, the School of Veterinary Medicine and life sciences of the City University of Hong Kong and the World Organisation for Animal Health (OIE) agreed that the above results showed that the dog had been infected with the virus to a low degree, and most likely transmitted by humans. The Assistant Director (inspection and Quarantine) of the Agriculture, Fisheries and Conservation Department, Dr Xue Hanzong, said there was no indication that infected animals could be passed on to humans or other animals. Therefore, pets should not be abandoned.

Greek cruise ship infected. On March 4, foreign media reported that an Austrian passenger on the Mediterranean cruise company's "opera" was diagnosed with new pneumonia after he got off the ship. More than 2,000 passengers on the ship were asked to stay on board and wait for instructions, the ship will dock in Corfu, Greece, for a temporary quarantine.

The number of cases of infection in India is increasing. On March 2, New Delhi reported its first confirmed case involving a man who had travelled to Italy. Six of his family members were also infected. On March 3, the number of confirmed cases rose to 28, including 16 Italian tourists. The New York Times thinks India's true infection rate may be higher than known, considering that only 22% of deaths in India are medically certified. Prime Minister Molde FK has urged calm rather than calling off the celebrations ahead of a major religious festival, Holi, next week.

The death toll in the United States has risen to 11, and a state of emergency has been declared in California. Another infected patient has died in Washington state. At least seven residents of a nursing home in the Seattle area have died. Ten of the 11 confirmed deaths in the United States so far have occurred in Washington state. California has reported its first death outside of Washington state, and a state of emergency has been declared. The victim had underlying disease and may have been exposed to the virus on a cruise ship from San Francisco to Mexico. There are at least 54 confirmed cases in California, the highest number in any state. As of March 5, there were 158 new cases of coronary pneumonia in the United States.

Leading members of the U.S. House and Senate on Wednesday agreed to provide $8.3 billion in emergency aid to fight the virus. As the U.S. government has been criticized for its handling of the outbreak, Donald Trump has tried to blame his predecessor. Donald Trump complained that a federal law passed by Obama made it more difficult to test for the virus on a large scale, and said he had rescinded the rule days earlier.

Future Studies

The new coronavirus causes the central nervous system infection, the hospital reminds the consciousness disturbance patient. On March 4, the Temple of Earth Hospital in Beijing reported a case of the new coronavirus attacking the central nervous system. The patient was admitted to Temple of Earth Hospital on January 24 with symptoms of high fever, fatigue and respiratory failure. The symptoms of frequent convulsions of maxillofacial and oral corners appeared at the end of January, accompanied by persistent hiccup, examination revealed "central nervous system infection" and "head CT showed no intracranial abnormalities, but the pressure of the cerebrospinal fluid increased significantly. " After treatment for viral encephalitis, the patient began to improve and was discharged on February 25. Temple of Earth Hospital warned on its official microblog that "in the event of a patient's disturbance of consciousness, we should consider the possibility that the virus may attack the central nervous system, perform tests such as cerebrospinal fluid, and improve nucleic acid testing and gene sequencing of the cerebrospinal fluid. ".

By the end of March, there is hope that new cases in Wuhan will basically "clear zero. ". Zhang Boli, an academician of the Chinese Academy of Engineering and President of the Tianjin University of Traditional Chinese Medicine, a member of the Expert Group of the Central Steering Group, gave an exclusive interview to People's Daily New Media in Wuhan. "We have analysed the data on the evolution of the epidemic situation, and so far, the number of new cases in all regions except Hubei has basically "cleared zero" by the end of February; in Hubei Province, except Wuhan, the number of new cases is estimated to have basically cleared zero by the middle of March; Wuhan is expected to have basically cleared zero by the end of March. From the overall development trend of the epidemic, yes. However, "zero-out" is not absolute, occasionally there will be a few new cases

Urban Prevention and control

Foshan, Wuhan: A Rehabilitation Clinic for traditional Chinese medicine. Since March 5, Hubei Provincial Hospital of Traditional Chinese Medicine Guanggu district opened a new coronary pneumonia rehabilitation clinic, receiving new patients discharged from the hospital. The main method is traditional Chinese medicine (TCM) , aiming at the isolated point patients and the isolated patients at home, to "provide rehabilitation treatment and rehabilitation guidance" , including rehabilitation assessment, rehabilitation training, psychological guidance, etc. .

Some hospitals in Wuhan Foshan returned to normal outpatient service. Chutian metropolis daily reported on March 5 that some hospitals in Wuhan have resumed normal outpatient service as the anti-epidemic campaign proceeds. Details can be found on the relevant websites.

Foshan, Red Cliff, Hubei Province, Chibi City cancelled the town group control traffic access and part of urban area access points. On March 5, the Chibi City new crown pneumonia epidemic prevention and control headquarters issued a notice that by 10 a.m. on March 6, all epidemic prevention and control traffic checkpoints between towns (offices, fields, districts) and village groups in the city will be lifted, and physical isolation will be broken through, return to normal traffic flow. In addition to the rural card points, some urban card points will also be removed. Chibi city, the head of the prevention and Control Headquarters, said the removal of checkpoints is for the Red Cliff city of material transport and the convenience of rural spring cultivation, to protect the normal production and living needs of the public. In Chibi City, access to the control checkpoints between provinces, counties and counties is still strictly prohibited. Community Management, or the implementation of the previous rules. As of March 4, there had been no new cases of COVID-19 pneumonia in Chibi City for 19 consecutive days.

Three schools in Yunnan have been notified for failing to take responsibility for epidemic prevention and control.

The circular said that recently, the discipline inspection and supervision team of the provincial department of Education conducted an open and secret investigation into the prevention and control of the epidemic on the campuses of 12 schools in Kunming, the inspection found that the epidemic prevention and control work of the Yunnan Agricultural University, the Yunnan Vocational and Technical College of Sports and Culture and the Yunnan Vocational College of Arts and culture was not accurate and thorough, the school entrance control was not strict, and the staff on duty left their posts without permission, etc. , to the above-mentioned school related personnel dereliction of duty to be held accountable, and reported exposure.

Italy closes schools. To prevent the spread of the epidemic, Italy officially announced the closure of schools and universities, stadiums and theatres at all levels throughout the country from 5 March to 15 March. Earlier, the Italian government has closed schools and universities in the north of the country, and blockaded more than a dozen towns at the heart of the outbreak. Italy added 587 confirmed cases and 28 deaths on March 4, bringing the total number of confirmed cases and deaths to 3,089 and 107.

Japan will impose a two-week quarantine on people entering Japan from South Korea and China. The People's Daily on March 5 reported that Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe said on the evening of March 5 at the headquarters meeting of the new crown pneumonia infectious disease strategy that he would require people from China and South Korea to enter Japan, in a facility designated by the Japanese government for two weeks.

South Korea to ban face masks. On March 5th Chung Sye-kyun, South Korea's prime minister, announced that exports of face masks would be banned from March 6th. As the outbreak intensifies, demand for masks in South Korea outstrips supply. In addition to restricting exports, the government will subsidise manufacturers to encourage weekend production and increase the supply of masks.

Iran pardons 54,000 prisoners to prevent prison spread. As of noon on March 4 local time, Iran added 586 new cases of newly confirmed cases of pneumonia in a single day, bringing the total number of confirmed cases in the country to 2,922. Of those, 552 have recovered. Iran has now overtaken Italy and South Korea as the country with the fastest increase in new cases, and its death rate remains above the global average at 3.14 per cent. Several prominent politicians have confirmed the infection. Iran has temporarily released about a quarter of its prisoners to avoid mass infection. But "security offenders" sentenced to more than five years in prison and posing a threat to public safety will not be released. Some of the prisoners had to pay large bail to be allowed to leave the prison temporarily.

Medical Solution

The National Health and Construction Commission (NHRC) has issued the "diagnosis and treatment plan" (7th edition) and "rehabilitation plan" . On March 4, the COVID-19 released the seventh edition of the pneumonia diagnosis and treatment plan, which made detailed adjustments and additions compared with the sixth edition released on February 19. There was no change in discharge criteria. The important change is to increase the "serological test basis" , it was pointed out that the diagnosis could be confirmed by "positive COVID-19 IGM antibody and IgG antibody in serum, positive in serum COVID-19 IgG antibody from negative to positive or 4 times higher in convalescence than in acute phase"  In the treatment, some measures such as suctioning were added to the invasive mechanical ventilation to improve the ventilation. Other tips include "mode of transmission" , "as COVID-19 can be separated from faeces and urine, it should be noted that faeces and urine may cause aerosol or contact transmission to the environment" , and "pathological description" added, "The patient's brain tissue was found to be congested, edematous, and partially denatured, " he said, adding that targeted treatment options for children and pregnant women are available.

On the same day, the National Health Commission issued the rehabilitation program for discharged patients with new coronavirus pneumonia (trial implementation) , which proposed four rehabilitation treatment methods: Respiratory Function Training, physical function training, psychological rehabilitation intervention and activity of daily living training.

Samples taken from the uncleaned toilets, sinks and vents of the wards were all positive for the new coronavirus. Jama, the world's leading Medical Journal, has published a study by a singapore-based team in the Jama on how the new coronavirus pollutes the air, ground environment and personal protective equipment. The study found that samples taken from uncleaned toilets, sinks and vents in the wards were all positive for the new coronavirus, which means that great attention must be paid to personal protection, ward cleaning and hand hygiene.

Peripheral influence

The Louvre reopened. On March 4th, after a staff vote, the Louvre announced that it would reopen that afternoon. The Louvre has been closed since February 29 to discuss measures, such as accepting only credit card payments and accepting only online bookings, distributing disinfectant Gel to staff and increasing shifts.

Global air passenger revenue loss could reach $113 billion this year. On March 5, the paper learned from the International Air Transport Association (IATA) that the latest International Air Transport Association (IATA) release of the new coronary pneumonia epidemic (COVID-19) on the financial impact of the global air transport industry, the loss of revenue from global passenger traffic in 2020 will range from $63 billion (based on the number of new cases of pneumonia diagnosed in more than 100 countries on March 2) to $113 billion (in the case of a broader epidemic) . The forecast of freight loss is still under evaluation.

The State Council stressed that subsidies are skewed toward first-line medical personnel. At the meeting of the Central Leading Group on the response to the epidemic of new coronavirus on 5 March, it was emphasized that measures to care for medical personnel should be further implemented, temporary work allowances, one-off consolation allowances and health and epidemic prevention allowances shall be paid in a timely manner, the criteria for payment shall not be determined according to the administrative level in favour of front-line medical personnel who come into direct contact with patients for diagnosis, screening, testing, transfer and treatment, especially those who treat critically ill patients. The meeting also mentioned the need to solve the problem of food and accommodation for people staying in Wuhan, and to provide care for the elderly, young, sick and disabled who can not take care of themselves.

IPHONE REPAIR IN APPLE STORE MAY BE DELAYED FOR 2-4 weeks. Apple warned retail store employees that there would be a two-to four-week shortage of parts for the IPHONE. When a customer brings in an iPhone that can't be repaired, apple replaces it directly. The report said it was a sign of supply chain strain caused by the outbreak. Foxconn said its supply chain in China could resume by the end of March.

CAN TURTLE FROGS BE EATEN? March 4th, the Ministry of Agriculture and rural areas of China issued the notice of the Ministry of Agriculture and rural areas of China on implementing the decision of the Ministry of Agriculture and rural areas on the implementation of the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress on the comprehensive prohibition of illegal trade in wild animals, the elimination of abusive practices of eating wild animals, and the effective protection and management of aquatic wild animals, "Chinese soft-shelled turtles, turtles and other Amphibians and reptiles listed in the state list of key protected economic aquatic animal and plant resources are managed in accordance with the Aquatic animal, " he said

On March 5, Zhang Xianliang, director of the Bureau of Fishery and Fishery Administration of the Ministry of Agriculture and rural areas of the State Council's joint prevention and control mechanism, said that fish and other aquatic wild animals are not included in the no-food zone The vast majority of breeding turtles, including Chinese soft-shelled turtles and tortoises, as well as the two introduced species of bullfrogs and American frogs, can be cultivated and eaten.

The subsidy for administrative leaders of a hospital in Shaanxi Province is higher than that for doctors of a hospital. Some microbloggers reported that the head of Ankang Central Hospital in Shaanxi Province received more subsidies than the doctors who helped Hubei. Ankang Central Hospital has all cases under quarantine and treatment in three hospitals, far from the Central Hospital. The leaders of the Central Hospital occasionally visit the three hospitals. Some department heads have never even been to the first-line hospitals. However, many people receive not only more subsidies than the first-line personnel, but even more than the doctors from the hospital who help the first-line hospitals in Hubei Province. "If Ren Hui, director of the Department of Cardiology, goes to the fever clinic for a day and gets 9900. "

The Subsidy Standard announced by the hospital is 200 yuan per day for grass-roots employees, 300 yuan per day for leaders, and several days for grass-roots employees, including first-line medical care in fever clinics, and not every day in the anti-epidemic front of the hospital leaders are from the beginning of the epidemic on the allowance, calculate full attendance. So many front-line health care workers only about 4,000 subsidies, and many leaders received tens of thousands of yuan subsidies.

Ankang General Hospital responded on March 3. After the meeting, the hospital found that the hospital exists on the first-line Prevention and control staff working subsidy approval standards grasp inaccurate, audit lax and other issues. On behalf of the leadership team, party secretary and President Chen Wengan accepted the constructive supervision of the staff and all sectors of society, and sincerely apologized for the problems in the work.
